Very good game, but it doesn't tally winnings properly. When you win a hand, your balance should go up, but it doesn't. Very strange. Still, I love it as a way to play blackjack without losing my shirt.

A good game that moves rapidly. The graphics are good with the exception that the cards are far too small. There is plenty of space to double the size or even triple the size of the cards, which would make them much easier to read. I like the immediate correction and explanation for wrong moves. I also like the easy availability of the Key tables.

Best blackjack app I've found. Doesn't eat up data in background and doesn't demand access to a lot of unrelated info on my device. Just wish it would work in landscape mode, and wish there was a setting for non-instructional game play and no limit on number of hands.   Word to the wise: blackjack rules and odds favor the dealer. Even if you do everything right, you'll usually lose.

content: This really is a trainer. If you play the drills you will learn. In addition to earning the mechanics of the game, it shows you that being correct doesn't always mean winning a particular hand. Sometimes your correct and you still lose. I appreciate the reality lesson.
So far so good, learnt a lot about play so far, as a complete novice, would be good if it explained what doubling and splitting meant but a good app well worth the money =)
Exercises the funemental. No speed control, but it does have different speeds. Essential tool.

Best BJ app Ive played! My mind could only hold so much information and other apps confuse me by allowing me to guess. I just swipe the strategy card out easily and quickly before making my move learning only the correct move. I luv how it allows u to practice pairs and while doing so, I learn the other hands a little at a time.  This app teaches u how to play correctly. Others apps correct u after u have made the wrong move or are too complicated to look at the strategy card before making a move. My #1.
